divs: Sighting DetailsExtremely bright object at high altitude, traveling at a moderate speed, from NW to SE from Greene County into Lenoir county, disapeared when attempted to digital video record. Object did not appear to be a shooting star nor an aircraft. No aircraft identification lights were observed. An aircraft was traveling perpendicular to the travel path of the object but was obviously smaller, and at a lower altitude with aircraft identification lights. 1. I had just walked out onto the back porch which faces almost due south. 2. When I gout at night, I always look up at the sky to observe the stars. 3. Unidentified, possibly the Space Station or the Shuttle. Ihave no idea if it has landed yet. 4. Described in opening paragraph. 5. Attempted to call daughter to let her know, no answer; then called X wife to share this with her. 5. Described in opening paragraph.
